Design your service using UK Parliament styles, components and patterns
Use this design system to make your service consistent with UK Parliament. Learn from the research and experience of other teams and avoid repeating work thatâ€™s already been done.

Styles
Make your service look like UK Parliament with guides for applying layout, typography, colour and images.

Browse styles

Components
Save time with reusable, accessible components for forms, navigation, panels, tables and more.

Browse components



Patterns
Help users complete common tasks like entering names and addresses, filling in forms and creating accounts.

Browse patterns




Status of styles/components/patterns

As these guidelines are a 'work in progress', we have labelled each component/pattern with a level of what the design team consider a probability of change e.g. some components/patterns need more work and will have a high probability of change, those that are considered more complete will have a high level of confidence associated with it, having a low probability of change.


Status

Changes are probable. Probability of change =  HIGH

Status

Some changes are probable. Probability of change = MEDIUM

Status

Confident in pattern. Probability of change = LOW



